  "prompt": "Which are the top startups in India?",
  "response": "As of the latest data available up to 2023, several Indian startups have made significant impacts and are often highlighted for their innovation, growth, and influence across various sectors. Here are some of the top Indian startups that have gained prominence:\n\n1. **Flipkart** - Originally an e-commerce company, Flipkart has expanded into a wide array of services and is considered one of India's largest online retailers.\n\n2. **Ola** - A leading ride-sharing platform, Ola is a major competitor to Uber in India and has expanded into other transport solutions, including electric vehicles and financial services.\n\n3. **Paytm** - Specializing in digital payments and financial services, Paytm has grown to become a leading fintech company with its wallet, payment bank, and financial products.\n\n4. **Byju\u2019s** - An education technology company that offers online tutoring and coaching for a variety of competitive exams and school subjects.\n\n5. **Zomato** - A major player in the food tech industry, Zomato provides food delivery services, restaurant information, and user reviews.\n\n6. **Swiggy** - Competing with Zomato, Swiggy focuses on food delivery, logistics, and connecting customers with restaurants.\n\n7. **OYO Rooms** - A leading hospitality chain, OYO offers budget accommodation by standardizing rooms and providing them under a single brand.\n\n8. **Udaan** - A B2B e-commerce platform that aims to connect small businesses, manufacturers, and traders with a range of services.\n\n9. **Razorpay** - A rapidly growing financial technology company offering payment solutions for businesses, including payment gateway services, payroll, and lending.\n\n10. **Dream11** - A fantasy sports platform that has gained a large user base, offering contests for various sports including cricket, football, and basketball.\n\nThese startups have been known for their innovation, substantial investment, and widespread impact. Keep in mind that the startup ecosystem is dynamic, and new players continually emerge. Regional variations in recognition and other emerging startups can also influence these rankings over time.",
